		<h1 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading-xl">
			Standard Payment Terms & Conditions
		</h1>

		<p><small>Last updated on 23/03/2026</small></p>
	</header>

	<div class="details space-y-8 spacer-b-md">

		<p>These terms apply to all web design and development services provided by Ryan Roberts trading as Yep Digital. Maintenance and hosting services are subject to separate terms, details of which are provided at the time of engagement.</p>

		<h2 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading spacer-t-xs">
			Payment Schedule
		</h2>
		<ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-4 md:pl-5 space-y-4">
			<li>For projects with a formal proposal, a 50% deposit is required before work commences. A further 25% is due upon design approval. The remaining 25% is payable upon completion of web development.</li>
			<li>Payment schedules may vary for smaller engagements and will be outlined on the relevant invoice or quote.</li>
			<li>Payment is by bank transfer, payable within 14 days of invoice date. All necessary account details will be included on each invoice.</li>
			<li>I am not currently VAT registered; no VAT will be charged unless my VAT status changes, in which case you will be notified.</li>
			<li>Invoices not settled within 14 days are subject to statutory interest at 8% above the UK base rate, in accordance with the Late Payment of Commercial Debts Act 1998. I reserve the right to pause work on any project where an invoice remains outstanding.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading spacer-t-xs">
			Scope & Additional Costs
		</h2>

		<ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-4 md:pl-5 space-y-4">
			<li>Additional commercial resources required for the project, including stock photography, commercial fonts, or third-party plugins, are not included in the quoted costs. These will be estimated and agreed in writing before any costs are incurred.</li>
			<li>Should the agreed scope change during the project, I will assess the impact on budget and timeline and discuss options before proceeding. Significant scope changes may incur additional charges.</li>
			<li>Out-of-scope work is billed at my standard hourly rate. This includes major design revisions, significant new features, or third-party integrations not covered in the original quote.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading spacer-t-xs">
			Client Responsibilities
		</h2>

		<ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-4 md:pl-5 space-y-4">
			<li>The client is responsible for providing all required content, including copy, images, logins, and third-party account access, in a timely manner. Delays caused by late or incomplete provision of materials may affect the project timeline, for which I accept no liability.</li>
			<li>Where project completion or launch is dependent on actions by the client, including domain transfers, hosting setup, or third-party account configuration, the quoted timeline is contingent on those being completed promptly. Delays outside my control will not affect agreed payment schedules.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading spacer-t-xs">
			Project Delays & Cancellation
		</h2>

		<ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-4 md:pl-5 space-y-4">
			<li>If the project is delayed for more than 30 consecutive days due to the client failing to provide required materials, feedback, or approvals, I reserve the right to treat the project as inactive. Reactivation may be subject to revised timelines and a restart fee. Any outstanding invoices remain due regardless of project status.</li>
			<li>If the project is cancelled after work has commenced, any deposit paid is non-refundable. Where no deposit was taken, an invoice will be raised for all work completed to date, with payment due within 14 days of cancellation. Work is deemed to have commenced upon the earlier of: the project kick-off, delivery of any materials by either party, or 5 working days after the deposit is received.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading spacer-t-xs">
			Intellectual Property & Usage Rights
		</h2>
		<p>Upon receipt of final payment, the client will own the overall creative design of the completed website. Certain components remain the property of their respective creators, including:</p>
		<ul class="list-disc list-outside pl-4 md:pl-5 space-y-4">
			<li>Code libraries, frameworks, and any intellectual property developed prior to or independently of the project.</li>
			<li>Photography, stock media, and visual assets licensed from third-party providers.</li>
			<li>Third-party software, plugins, or tools used in the development or hosting of the website.</li>
		</ul>

		<h2 class="font-bold tracking-[-0.0125em] text-white text-heading spacer-t-xs">
			Governing Law
		</h2>
		<p>These terms are governed by the laws of Scotland. Any disputes arising from work carried out under these terms shall be subject to the exclusive jurisdiction of the Scottish courts.</p>

		<p>If you have any questions, feel free to get in touch at <a href="mailto:ryan@yep.digital">ryan@yep.digital</a>.</p>

